The paper deals with the game theoretic approach to distributed control, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). It specifically focuses on the design of local utility functions for resource allocation problems, which is a topic within distributed computing (cs.DC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of distributed algorithms and the computation of Nash equilibria, which are topics within machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.NE).
